# AI-assisted workflow (Orbit Wars)

Adapted from [cursorrules-collection `practices/ai-assisted-development.mdc`](https://github.com/nedcodes-ok/cursorrules-collection/blob/main/rules-mdc/practices/ai-assisted-development.mdc). Stack facts stay in `orbit-wars.mdc` + `AGENTS.md`.

## Context to include

- Task + paths: `src/jax/train/`, `conf/training/`, `tests/test_feature_encoding_golden.py`.
- Point to `docs/AGENT_CAPABILITIES.md`, `make agent-context` for session JSON.
- One task per prompt; pin only relevant files.

## Verification commands (in order)

1. `uv sync --group dev`
2. After code change: `make test-fast` or `make test-domain-*`
3. Config change: `uv run ow train print_resolved_config=true`
4. Gates/benchmarks only when user requests GPU/time

## Generation habits

- Ask for tests with behavior changes; use existing golden/markers patterns.
- Prefer `ow` subcommands (`ow runs watch`, `ow eval status`, `ow benchmark gate run`) over new `scripts/*.py`.
- Read every diff before accept; watch for hallucinated JAX APIs or wrong metric denominators.

## Rules maintenance

- Keep `.mdc` files focused; stack-specific truth stays in `orbit-wars.mdc` + `AGENTS.md`.
- Update rules when the same mistake repeats (bare `pytest -n`, v1 feature paths).
